This paper discusses risk-based testing approaches and their application to various testing standards. It involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it deals with testing software systems. It also involves computer security (cs.CR) as it discusses risk-based testing for security testing. Quality assurance (cs.QA) is another likely category as the paper discusses tailoring testing approaches to meet specific quality requirements. The paper also involves systems and information theory (cs.SI) as it discusses the use of fuzzy expert systems in risk-based testing. Finally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it discusses the use of various algorithms and techniques for risk-based testing.
